The paper proposes a new deep learning architecture for classification and regression tasks, with a focus on representation learning and flexibility. The architecture incorporates a stochastic routing framework and introduces a probabilistic pruning technique to reduce unnecessary computation. The paper also proposes a specified version of the architecture for efficiency, which utilizes sparse convolution operation. Given these characteristics, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
